# Security & Authorization

## Non-negotiables

- **SudoCache** — Use for sudo session management. Never store sudo passwords.
- **ValidationLayer** — Validate all user-facing and external input before processing.
- **LootManager** — Store handshakes, passwords, credentials encrypted; never plain text.
- **Parameterized queries** — All SQL must use parameters; no string concatenation for user input.
- **Authorization** — Privileged ops gated by AuthPort/sudo cache; no silent privilege escalation.

## Do not

- Commit secrets, API keys, or credentials.
- Log sensitive data (passwords, tokens, full handshakes).
- Weaken security controls or skip validation to “simplify” code.

Run a lightweight secrets scan before push. Reference: PROJECT_RULES.md, AGENTS.md.
